Conventions and units used within this data release for : Phys.Rev.D 104 (2021) 9, 092007

Issues with the data release, contact:
Daniel Ruterbories druterbo@pas.rochester.edu or druterbo@gmail.com
Kevin McFarland kevin@rochester.edu


Binning can be found in bin_mapping.txt which describes the relationship between p||,pt and global_bin_indicies. You can also determin bin width from this file.

IMPORTANT: All cross sections and uncertainties in these files are differential cross sections and as such are divided by bin areas(width). IF you want to make Figures 9 and 10 in the paper you will need to remove the area(width) normalization and integrate over the perpendicular axis. 

-----------------------------------------------------


Data Cross Section, Figure 13, is saved in data_result_ptpl_2D_minerva_inclusive_6GeV.txt

The data in this CSV files is: longitudinal muon momentum (GeV/c), transverse muon momentum (GeV/c), differential cross section cm^2/(GeV/c)^2, statistical uncertainty cm^2/(GeV/c)^2, total uncertainty (stat. + systematic) cm^2/(GeV/c)^2

Values of exactly 0.00E+00 are unreported bins.


-------------------------------------------------------


Covariance matrices are provided for:
total uncertainty: cov_ptpl_minerva_inclusive_6GeV_total.txt
total uncertainty in ROOT TMatrix format for precision: cov_ptpl_minerva_inclusive_6GeV.root
statistical uncertainty: cov_ptpl_minerva_inclusive_6GeV_stat.txt
flux uncertainty: cov_ptpl_minerva_inclusive_6GeV_flux.txt
muon energy scale uncertainty: cov_ptpl_minerva_inclusive_6GeV_energyscale.txt

Each file contains a csv of: global_bin_index_i , global_bin_index_j, covariance (cm^2/(GeV/c)^2)^2.

Values of exactly 0.00E+00 are unreported bins. To invert the matrix you either need to use a numerical method that is able to handle singular matrices or remove unreported bins and rework the bin mapping.


---------------------------------------------------------


Cross sections for model predictions described in Figures 15,16,17,18 are provided in the model_ptpl*.txt files.

The format is: longitudinal muon momentum (GeV/c), transverse muon momentum (GeV/c), differential cross section cm^2/(GeV/c)^2


